  "texts": [
    "From the initial phases of natural language processing, when computers followed strict guidelines or relied mostly on their human created traits, we have advanced greatly.",
    "Though often useful, these traditional approaches ran up challenges with irony, ambiguity & the always shifting dynamics of human language.",
    "Driven by huge datasets and sophisticated training approaches, the arrival of LLMs marked a change from rule-based systems to models that learn from examples.",
    "Along with that change came the latest challenge: how best can we interact with these models?",
    "Prompt engineering plays this function.Prompt engineering essentially consists in the creation of inputs that guide a large language model to produce useful, exact, and contextually too many relevant outputs."
  ],
